page.title: 05CLUBS AND ASSOCIATIONS
page.content: A large majority of people in the D_block enjoy sport eg. football,tennis,cricket.Nature associations and clubs are also very popular,perhaps because of the people living in the country_side.Interst in art and music is only slight,only five people mentioning it on the questionaire returns. Leisure activities appear very popular,for example Womens Institute and camping.Perhaps being in the South West means it being lovely and sunny and able to do most outdoor activities.Only nine were involved in charities like Save the Children and Oxfam. Quite a few people are associated with the services,like the Marines and the Navy. Benjamin Gilpin,age:11.
